UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. James Junior FINCH, Defendant-Appellee. No. 75-2149. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 19, 1977. Revised July 29, 1977. Keith L. Burrowes, Asst. U. S. Atty., Billings, Mont., argued for plaintiff-appellant. Robert W. Holmstrom, argued, Longan & Holmstrom, Billings, Mont., for defendant-appellee.

Before CHAMBERS and KENNEDY, Circuit Judges, and WONG,* District Judge.

Honorable Dick Yin Wong, United States District Judge for the District of Hawaii, sitting by designation.

Pursuant to the decision of the Supreme Court of the United States in Finch v. United States, - U.S. -, 97 S.Ct. 2909, 53 L.Ed.2d 1048 (1977) (per curiam), the appeal is DISMISSED.
